---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: UK NHS Number Input
description: an input for entering a UK NHS number
---

{% from "components/united-kingdom-national-health-service-number-input/macro.njk" import unitedKingdomNationalHealthServiceNumberInput %}
{% from "components/label/macro.njk" import label %}
{% from "components/hint/macro.njk" import hint %}
{% from "components/field/macro.njk" import field %}

<h2>Default</h2>
{% call field() %}
  {{ label({ for: "nhs", text: "NHS number" }) }}
  {{ hint({
    id: "nhs-hint",
    text: "It is a 10-digit number on any letter from the NHS."
  }) }}
  {{ unitedKingdomNationalHealthServiceNumberInput({
    id: "nhs",
    describedBy: "nhs-hint"
  }) }}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Pre-filled (grouped format accepted)</h2>
{% call field() %}
  {{ label({ for: "nhs2", text: "NHS number" }) }}
  {{ unitedKingdomNationalHealthServiceNumberInput({
    id: "nhs2",
    value: "485 777 3456"
  }) }}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Accessibility note</h2>
<p>The macro sets <code>inputmode="numeric"</code> so mobile devices
  show the numeric keypad, <code>autocomplete="off"</code> because
  browsers have no standardised token for medical-record numbers,
  and <code>spellcheck="false"</code> to suppress irrelevant spell
  check highlighting.</p>
